text: Don t let it ruin your night  Ok this is so random  but just wanted to tell y all because i ve been thinking about this  And this refers to short term relationships btw   Going through a breakup is hard  Getting broken up with is painful  It hurts  I hate it when people say  aww don t let it ruin your night  or  don t cry  to someone who has just been broken up with  Of course it s gonna ruin their night  Of course they are going to cry  It is so fake and apathetic to say that to someone  even though obviously I know people are just trying to help  Rather  this is the point I like to try and get across Of course this is going to ruin your night  And that s ok  This is something worth crying about  You can cry on my shoulder if you want  But once you have let it all out  cried all of your tears and gotten through the painful moment  it s time to move on  But  you can only move on once you let out all of your emotions and deal with what you are going through rather than bottling them up  So right now  cry  Be upset  Accept that this breakup is happening  and react to the situation  Tomorrow morning  wake up with a fresh point of view and start thinking about how you can move forward You can t just brush breakups off and pretend they didn t happen  Because they did  But that s ok  Instead  take the time to accept it  You can only move forward once you deal with the past   I don t know if that s the right way of saying things  but that s my point  Let me know if you agree
